Touring Vancouver CategoryPage Best Food in Town Beautiful Parks Beaches Everywhere Entertainment Galore
//Beaches Wreck Beach is a popular clothing-optional beach located in Pacific Spirit Regional Park, which is in turn part of the University Endowment Lands just west of Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada. A Vancouver beach located west of the seaside neighbourhood of Kitsilano. It is surrounded by Jericho Beach Park, a grassy area with a pond, which is a picnic destination. Kitsilano Beach is one of the most popular beaches in Vancouver, especially in the warm summer months. Located at the north edge of the Kitsilano neighbourhood, the beach faces out onto Burrard Inlet. English Bay is located in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, west of the downtown peninsula and False Creek. It consists of the south side of the Burrard Inlet, extending from Point Grey in the southwest to Prospect Point in the northeast.
//Parks Stanley Park is a 405-hectare public park that borders the downtown of Vancouver in British Columbia, Canada and is almost entirely surrounded by waters of Vancouver Harbour and English Bay. Central Park is a 90-hectare urban park in Burnaby, British Columbia, founded in 1891. The park is on the Vancouver-Burnaby border, just west of the Metropolis. Always bursting with activity, Grandview Park is often the site of community activities, from picnics and plays to festivals and concerts. In 2011, the park was upgraded with a new playground, pathways, stage, sport court, field house with accessible washrooms, lawns, gardens and restored cenotaph area. Great place for dog walks, hang outs, romantic strolls, clearing your head, taking in the people and sounds and beauty of Trout Lake is a perfect way to spend some hours
//Games The Rio Theatre is an independent, multidisciplinary art house in Vancouver, BC, Canada, built in 1938. FlyOver Canada is an amazing virtual flight ride in which you will “take off” into a huge domed screen to enjoy a breathtaking flight across Canada’s most spectacular sights. Science World at Telus World of Science, Vancouver is a science centre run by a not-for-profit organization in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada. The Vancouver Aquarium is a public aquarium located in Stanley Park in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada.
//Foods High-end steaks and an extensive wine list are offered in a snazzy art deco setting with a lounge. Late-night counter-serve nook serving inventive specialty pies and slices in an unfussy interior. Sushiyama is a popular Japanese Restaurant near Kingsway and Broadway. They serve up affordable Japanese dishes. Neighborhood hangout with rustic decor and sports on TV serving burgers, wings and drinks.
